1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,560
 Thank you, Carla.

2
00:00:01,560 --> 00:00:03,080
 Good morning, church.

3
00:00:03,080 --> 00:00:04,100
 >> Good morning. >> Good morning.

4
00:00:04,100 --> 00:00:06,300
 Good morning, those who are joining online.

5
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:08,800
 So it's a great privilege to,

6
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:11,440
 we can open the word together this morning.

7
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:13,560
 So as Carla said just now,

8
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:18,560
 Pastor Andrew opened us a new sermon series on public faith.

9
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:23,080
 He asked us a question on what should a Christian do

10
00:00:23,080 --> 00:00:26,320
 when the world has gone crazy?

11
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:28,640
 So I think this is something that we are,

12
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:31,200
 I'm still wrestling with that

13
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,320
 since last week hearing this word.

14
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:36,480
 And he also showed us that we are actually

15
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:39,600
 called to be sought and liked,

16
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,720
 to live out our faith publicly,

17
00:00:41,720 --> 00:00:46,720
 to we feel the love of Jesus for the world.

18
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:49,040
 And today, we're going to look at

19
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:52,320
 a very important aspect of our life.

20
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:53,400
 In fact, the coming weeks,

21
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:56,760
 we will be looking into different areas of our life.

22
00:00:56,760 --> 00:01:00,600
 But today, we will focus on our work.

23
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:02,960
 So I believe most of us here

24
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:07,960
 spend the most hours of our week in our workplace, right?

25
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:12,160
 And two weeks ago, Pastor John also preached

26
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:14,400
 on the topic of workplace.

27
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:18,360
 And he focused on the aspect of how we are called,

28
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:22,580
 or we are all called to witness Jesus in our workplace.

29
00:01:22,580 --> 00:01:24,720
 And there's no such differentiation

30
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:27,040
 between sacred and secular.

31
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:30,080
 And we are all called to evangelize.

32
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:33,520
 And he gave us some great tips on how to do that as well.

33
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:36,140
 So if you have missed the past two weeks,

34
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:38,220
 I would encourage you to go back to YouTube

35
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:39,720
 and catch up on that.

36
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:44,520
 But today, we will look into the workplace

37
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:47,400
 from a very different perspective.

38
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:52,040
 So we will look into how we live out our faith publicly

39
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:55,840
 when we are actually doing our work.

40
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:59,080
 So let's say we all work eight hours per day.

41
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:02,720
 So I'm sure that we don't spend eight hours per day

42
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,480
 to evangelize, right?

43
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:09,620
 I would be worried if you do, unless you're a missionary.

44
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:11,900
 So just to say like, what,

45
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:14,200
 how do we live out our faith publicly

46
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:16,680
 when we are actually working,

47
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:19,520
 when we're actually doing our eight hour work

48
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,000
 during our day?

49
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:25,680
 As important as it is to evangelize in our workplace

50
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,280
 and to pray for our colleagues,

51
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:32,140
 this is not the only way to express our faith publicly.

52
00:02:32,140 --> 00:02:38,640
 So last week, Pastor Andrew emphasized on that,

53
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:41,720
 like being public about our faith

54
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:45,180
 can be reflected in our lifestyles,

55
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:51,360
 where our life can reflect the values,

56
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:55,760
 the behavior, and the character of Jesus.

57
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:59,040
 Can be shown in our choices we make each day,

58
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:02,480
 in our habits, in our character,

59
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:06,980
 in how we think, in how we use our resources.

60
00:03:06,980 --> 00:03:10,920
 So these can be reflected

61
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:13,460
 in how we work in our workplace as well.

62
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:17,600
 So how do we make our faith public

63
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:21,200
 when we are actually doing our daily work?

64
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:24,400
 How can we demonstrate our values as Christians

65
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,860
 when we are working?

66
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:31,860
 And how do we live as salt and light in the workplace,

67
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:35,640
 being a blessing to those who work alongside?

68
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:40,120
 So to answer these questions,

69
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:43,780
 maybe we perhaps need to take a step back

70
00:03:43,780 --> 00:03:48,360
 on how we think and how we approach our work.

71
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:53,360
 Over these years, I've heard a lot Christians

72
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:58,280
 struggle to see God and see the purposes in their work.

73
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,720
 And at some point, I struggle with that as well,

74
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,500
 if I'm honest.

75
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:05,520
 So before I joined the staff team of Divine,

76
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:08,320
 I actually was a paralegal for some years.

77
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:11,720
 So working in the legal industry

78
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:15,040
 could make me so occupied

79
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:19,100
 that I don't actually think about God much when I work.

80
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:24,680
 Especially at the start of my career.

81
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:28,540
 I remember in those days, I go back to the office,

82
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:32,400
 and all my attentions would go to my clients,

83
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:36,540
 my bosses, overwhelmed by emails and phone calls,

84
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:40,640
 people chasing me or telling me to do certain things.

85
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:44,720
 And I was so overwhelmed, my time was so occupied

86
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:47,760
 that I don't feel that I hear God much.

87
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:50,840
 Instead, I feel like I'm so occupied

88
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:54,200
 by the voices of everyone else.

89
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:57,620
 My bosses, my clients, the people around me.

90
00:04:57,620 --> 00:05:00,980
 I hear so many voices, but God.

91
00:05:00,980 --> 00:05:06,360
 So I felt very disconnected from my faith

92
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:08,900
 when I was actually working.

93
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:13,440
 So what I did was, FYI, I don't recommend this,

94
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:16,840
 I just fill my free time with a lot of Christian activities.

95
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:19,560
 When I get off work, go to my CG,

96
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,880
 of course go to Sunday services,

97
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:24,960
 I sign myself up to different Bible studies,

98
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:27,560
 I serve as well, so that I make sure my schedule

99
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:30,680
 is very occupied by Christian activities,

100
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:33,920
 so that I feel that I'm connected with God somehow,

101
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:34,760
 each day.

102
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:37,520
 But that was not sustainable,

103
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:39,960
 because I only had that much energy

104
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:41,840
 when I was in early 20s.

105
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:46,600
 But how can we do that?

106
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:50,720
 So just to say that, echoing with Andrew's

107
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:53,200
 four different approaches that Christians have,

108
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:56,500
 I was actually escaping from the reality

109
00:05:56,500 --> 00:06:00,200
 that I don't see God much in my workplace.

110
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,740
 He mentioned four different models

111
00:06:02,740 --> 00:06:04,500
 that Christians might approach

112
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:07,980
 when we are overwhelmed by the sins of the world,

113
00:06:07,980 --> 00:06:11,200
 of the darkness, and we might, like me,

114
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:16,200
 escape, or insulate, or we control, or we conform.

115
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:20,960
 So I believe each one of us is different,

116
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:22,600
 but somehow when we struggle,

117
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:26,400
 we might tempt it to do one of these things, right?

118
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:30,680
 I hope I'm not the only person feeling that way

119
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,640
 when we struggle at our work.

120
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:38,360
 So I've been hearing a lot of my friends,

121
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:42,120
 like they tell me, "Oh, when I come to Sunday services,

122
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:47,120
 "I feel super connected, I feel super spiritually recharged,

123
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:51,040
 "but on Monday, when I go back to my office,

124
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:54,500
 "that I feel disconnected again.

125
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:58,540
 "I really can't see God when I'm actually working."

126
00:06:58,540 --> 00:07:01,420
 But when we look at our bank account, perhaps,

127
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:03,920
 or our families, then we realize

128
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,700
 we really need to pay the bill,

129
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:09,520
 so we push ourselves through to continue to work,

130
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,280
 like maybe a little bit disconnected,

131
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:15,080
 or we feel spiritually and emotionally empty as we work,

132
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:18,920
 but we push ourselves through not feeling connected.

133
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:22,420
 Can you resonate with this?

134
00:07:22,420 --> 00:07:25,260
 But is this really everything about work?

135
00:07:25,260 --> 00:07:28,960
 We just, like seeing the purpose of work

136
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:32,140
 as earning the daily bread for us?

137
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:38,040
 Let's pause a moment and ask ourselves a question.

138
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:43,360
 What motivates us to go to work each day?

139
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:49,540
 And what motivates us to do the work each day?

140
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:57,340
 Paul in Colossians actually talks about

141
00:07:57,340 --> 00:07:59,800
 how we should approach our work.

142
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:02,800
 In fact, in the whole chapter three of Colossians,

143
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,820
 he talked about Jesus is risen,

144
00:08:05,820 --> 00:08:09,300
 and we are all raised with him,

145
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:12,180
 and he is calling us as Christians

146
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:15,580
 to put our sinful nature to death

147
00:08:15,580 --> 00:08:19,300
 and live fully for Jesus Christ.

148
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:21,980
 And then he talks about different relationships

149
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:25,220
 and how Christians should live for Jesus

150
00:08:25,220 --> 00:08:27,840
 in these relationships.

151
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,220
 And when he talks about the relationship

152
00:08:30,220 --> 00:08:34,160
 between slaves and masters, he says this.

153
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:38,440
 "Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart

154
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:42,740
 "as working for the Lord, not for human masters,

155
00:08:42,740 --> 00:08:46,000
 "since you know that you will receive an inheritance

156
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,440
 "from the Lord as a reward.

157
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:52,380
 "It is the Lord Christ you are serving."

158
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:56,740
 Here, Paul is shifting our perspective

159
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:58,980
 on how we should approach our work

160
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:02,060
 and work relationships as Christians.

161
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:05,820
 He calls us to see all that we are doing

162
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:07,980
 as a serving to Jesus,

163
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:13,340
 and we are to do everything for Jesus Christ

164
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:14,880
 with all our heart.

165
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:18,380
 But I do want to clarify one thing,

166
00:09:18,380 --> 00:09:21,500
 what Paul is not telling us to do.

167
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:25,940
 Paul is not asking us to tolerate slavery

168
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:28,480
 and injustice in our workplace.

169
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:34,180
 He's not calling us to just brainwash ourselves,

170
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:36,140
 oh, I'm working it for Jesus,

171
00:09:36,140 --> 00:09:39,380
 so I just continue to suffer as we work.

172
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:42,220
 This is not what we are called to do.

173
00:09:42,220 --> 00:09:47,220
 Instead, Paul is reminding us that Jesus is sovereign

174
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:51,480
 in every aspect of our lives,

175
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:55,640
 and he is bringing transformation to the world.

176
00:09:55,640 --> 00:10:00,180
 So he is calling us as Christians to work with him,

177
00:10:00,180 --> 00:10:03,560
 to live fully for Jesus

178
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:07,360
 so we can be part of God's redemptive work.

179
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:10,900
 So as we are working,

180
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:13,240
 our motivation shouldn't come from the world

181
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,700
 or come from our bosses.

182
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:19,600
 At the same time, we're not called to disregard everything

183
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,860
 about our human bosses either.

184
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:26,680
 But he is calling us to do this

185
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:31,540
 as we are rendering what is right and what is wrong.

186
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:35,420
 We should be considering what is fitting

187
00:10:35,420 --> 00:10:38,040
 in the Lord as our priority.

188
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:42,800
 So we need to think about this.

189
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,440
 As we look at our work,

190
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:47,800
 are we demonstrating the sovereignty of Jesus?

191
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:52,280
 Are we working as in we are working for Jesus?

192
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:56,600
 Is there a way for us as Christians to work

193
00:10:56,600 --> 00:11:00,420
 so that we can reflect Jesus is our Lord,

194
00:11:00,420 --> 00:11:02,600
 which is visible to others,

195
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,600
 to the people around us as well?

196
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:09,780
 What does it look like to be salt and light

197
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:13,460
 in our workplaces through the way we work

198
00:11:13,460 --> 00:11:17,580
 that reflect the heart and the character of Jesus?

199
00:11:17,580 --> 00:11:19,780
 So from these questions,

200
00:11:19,780 --> 00:11:22,780
 we can talk about a lot of different areas,

201
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:24,340
 a lot of different characters

202
00:11:24,340 --> 00:11:28,220
 that we can be more Christ-like at our work.

203
00:11:28,220 --> 00:11:32,660
 Jesus demonstrated and talked about different characters

204
00:11:32,660 --> 00:11:36,100
 which we can actually apply to our work.

205
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:38,520
 We can talk about humility,

206
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:43,120
 we can talk about generosity and patience,

207
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:46,180
 or even forgiveness in our workplace.

208
00:11:46,180 --> 00:11:48,400
 But today, I want to focus

209
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:50,740
 on one very specific characteristic,

210
00:11:50,740 --> 00:11:56,820
 which I feel it is very critical for us as Christians

211
00:11:56,820 --> 00:12:00,700
 to be salt and light and to be public about our faith.

212
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,620
 And I would like to call it

213
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:06,320
 the Christ-like, Christ-centered integrity.

214
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:10,080
 So when we hear about integrity,

215
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:12,180
 I don't know what comes to your mind.

216
00:12:12,180 --> 00:12:16,560
 In English, it means be honest and upright.

217
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:19,420
 And sometimes we use this word to describe someone

218
00:12:19,420 --> 00:12:21,680
 who demonstrate a very strong ethic.

219
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:26,360
 Any musical fans in this room?

220
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:32,860
 Oh, no musical fan in both 950, oh, Susanna, thank you.

221
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:34,780
 Some musical fans here.

222
00:12:34,780 --> 00:12:36,540
 So when I hear about this word,

223
00:12:36,540 --> 00:12:41,020
 or when people hear about this word, oopsie, nevermind.

224
00:12:41,020 --> 00:12:45,700
 So we might associate that with a character, thank you,

225
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:48,100
 in Les Mis, Les Miserables, who's Chauvet.

226
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:52,620
 He really is serious about his work

227
00:12:52,620 --> 00:12:54,300
 in a very legalistic way.

228
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:58,260
 He sees following the law as serving the Lord Jesus,

229
00:12:58,260 --> 00:13:02,580
 which is very sad to see that character.

230
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:04,220
 He's very uncompassionate.

231
00:13:04,220 --> 00:13:07,920
 It's very hard for him to receive grace as well.

232
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:09,360
 But I can talk about this forever,

233
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:11,500
 but this is not a point to say that.

234
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:14,220
 We can take integrity, something like this,

235
00:13:14,220 --> 00:13:15,740
 that to be upright,

236
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:19,460
 something to demonstrate a very strong ethic.

237
00:13:19,460 --> 00:13:22,040
 But in fact, in the Bible,

238
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:26,980
 the word integrity is so rich in its meaning.

239
00:13:26,980 --> 00:13:30,100
 So I would like to go into the Old Testament a little bit

240
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:34,900
 to see how the word integrity is used.

241
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:39,480
 So there are two ways, mostly, in the Old Testament

242
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:41,680
 of how to use this word integrity.

243
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:46,000
 And first, it appears as righteousness.

244
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,960
 Zedek, this word.

245
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:52,840
 So the word is used to describe someone

246
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:56,840
 who is morally aligned with God,

247
00:13:56,840 --> 00:14:00,400
 and someone whose integrity,

248
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,080
 I think we can understand this,

249
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:05,840
 morally aligned with God, morally upright and honest.

250
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:08,900
 But there's another way of using the word integrity

251
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:13,160
 in the Old Testament, which is tamam.

252
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:18,160
 So this word means to reach an end and to be completed.

253
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:22,060
 And the interesting thing is,

254
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:27,060
 it is frequently used in Leviticus and Numbers.

255
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:32,100
 The word is in reference to the sacrificial animals,

256
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:36,900
 which are without blemish and physically whole.

257
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:40,660
 So I wonder whether it rings a bell in you.

258
00:14:40,660 --> 00:14:46,480
 Because Jesus is the Lamb of sacrifice.

259
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:51,140
 He sacrificed fully for our sake.

260
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:55,700
 And same to us, we are called to be a living sacrifice

261
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:57,820
 to our Lord Jesus as well.

262
00:14:57,820 --> 00:15:03,580
 And are we giving our whole to Jesus?

263
00:15:03,580 --> 00:15:06,940
 If today we ask you to look at our work

264
00:15:06,940 --> 00:15:09,500
 as a sacrifice to Jesus,

265
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:14,120
 would you say you can offer a whole sacrifice to Jesus?

266
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:17,220
 I want to clarify this.

267
00:15:17,220 --> 00:15:20,080
 By giving our whole to Jesus at work

268
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:22,480
 doesn't mean that we work 24/7.

269
00:15:23,820 --> 00:15:28,820
 But it is about to be fully aligned to Jesus

270
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:33,800
 and submit to his sovereignty in all aspects

271
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,400
 of our lives and of our work.

272
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:41,180
 We are to align ourselves with his values

273
00:15:41,180 --> 00:15:46,080
 and with his characters in the work that we are doing,

274
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:49,440
 no matter how big or how small our work is.

275
00:15:51,140 --> 00:15:53,940
 Throughout these years of working in both corporate

276
00:15:53,940 --> 00:15:58,780
 and also ministry, I've seen and heard a lot of Christians

277
00:15:58,780 --> 00:16:01,420
 really desire to work fully for God.

278
00:16:01,420 --> 00:16:04,420
 I'm sure most of us here are like this.

279
00:16:04,420 --> 00:16:08,660
 We really want to work fully for Jesus,

280
00:16:08,660 --> 00:16:11,140
 but the environment is just so difficult

281
00:16:11,140 --> 00:16:13,940
 for us to be able to do that.

282
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:17,140
 Perhaps our biggest struggle in the work environment

283
00:16:17,140 --> 00:16:20,420
 is that the environment is so broken.

284
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:24,860
 It's full of brokenness, it's full of sins,

285
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:28,340
 full of unfairness in our workplace,

286
00:16:28,340 --> 00:16:33,340
 and it seems impossible to change in a short period of time.

287
00:16:33,340 --> 00:16:39,860
 And also it's so common to hear this in our workplace.

288
00:16:39,860 --> 00:16:42,740
 And sometimes I hear this from Christians as well.

289
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:47,340
 They will say, "I'm not paid enough to do my work."

290
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:51,140
 Or, "My boss is so mean to people."

291
00:16:51,140 --> 00:16:57,780
 Or, "The company is so unfair in different practices."

292
00:16:57,780 --> 00:17:02,980
 So we just lack of and not giving 100% to our work.

293
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:06,780
 Or you are seeing in your workplace

294
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:09,940
 that everyone is doing the bare minimum at work,

295
00:17:09,940 --> 00:17:13,340
 so you just do the same to be fair.

296
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:16,660
 Or everyone is taking advantage

297
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:19,340
 of the reimbursement system perhaps,

298
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:20,700
 so I just do the same.

299
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:28,340
 Perhaps you are thinking, "I will give my 100%

300
00:17:28,340 --> 00:17:33,020
 "when I get paid enough, or when I get a better boss,

301
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:36,540
 "or when my company is fair to me finally."

302
00:17:36,540 --> 00:17:39,540
 But I want to say this.

303
00:17:39,540 --> 00:17:45,780
 The reality is the world is not gonna be perfect.

304
00:17:46,540 --> 00:17:49,540
 We will never feel that we're paid enough.

305
00:17:49,540 --> 00:17:56,700
 And there's no perfect human boss or working environment.

306
00:17:56,700 --> 00:18:03,020
 With this mindset, we are depending on the environment

307
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:08,020
 to shape how we work, instead of allowing our faith

308
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:09,780
 to shape how we work.

309
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:13,900
 When we start to allow the environment

310
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:17,980
 to become our motivation, we are not offering

311
00:18:17,980 --> 00:18:21,060
 that whole sacrifice to Jesus at our work.

312
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:26,140
 And we have lost our calling to be salt

313
00:18:26,140 --> 00:18:27,940
 and light in this world.

314
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:32,980
 As Andrew shared last week, being salt and light

315
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:37,340
 is not only to be different from the world,

316
00:18:37,340 --> 00:18:40,900
 but also to bring changes to the world,

317
00:18:40,900 --> 00:18:45,900
 to add flavor to the world, to preserve the world

318
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:51,220
 from decaying, and also to bring light to the darkness.

319
00:18:51,220 --> 00:18:57,780
 If we are to let the environment to shape how we work,

320
00:18:57,780 --> 00:19:02,780
 we become darkness in the darkness and tasteless salt.

321
00:19:08,420 --> 00:19:13,420
 To unpack this further, I want to look into a parable

322
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:17,380
 to see the danger of letting the environment

323
00:19:17,380 --> 00:19:20,300
 to become our motivation at work.

324
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:25,300
 So we'll look into Luke chapter 16, one to eight.

325
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:28,900
 Jesus told his disciples, there was a rich man

326
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:33,380
 whose manager was accused of wasting his possessions.

327
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:36,140
 So he called him and asked him,

328
00:19:36,140 --> 00:19:38,820
 what is this I hear about you?

329
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:40,860
 Give an account of your management

330
00:19:40,860 --> 00:19:43,980
 because you cannot be manager any longer.

331
00:19:43,980 --> 00:19:48,820
 The manager said to himself, what shall I do now?

332
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:52,060
 My master is taking away my job.

333
00:19:52,060 --> 00:19:56,460
 I'm not strong enough to dig and I'm ashamed to beg.

334
00:19:56,460 --> 00:20:02,100
 I know what I'll do so that when I lose my job here,

335
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:05,480
 people will welcome me into their houses.

336
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:10,440
 So he called in each one of his master's debtors.

337
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:14,960
 He asked the first, how much do you owe my master?

338
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:17,640
 3000 liters of olive oil, he replied.

339
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:20,600
 The manager told him, take your bill,

340
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:24,480
 sit down quickly and make it 1500.

341
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:28,800
 Then he asked the second, and how much do you owe?

342
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,880
 30 tons of wheat, he replied.

343
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:35,320
 He told him, take your bill and make it 24.

344
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:38,680
 The master commended the dishonest manager

345
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:40,920
 because he acted shrewdly.

346
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:44,600
 For the people of this world are more shrewd

347
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:47,080
 in dealing with their own kind

348
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:49,760
 than are the people of the light.

349
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:53,680
 We might feel a little bit confused here, it's okay.

350
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:55,760
 Like after reading this parable,

351
00:20:55,760 --> 00:21:00,240
 we will break it down and see what is going on in this story.

352
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:03,720
 So this parable starts with a rich man

353
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:08,160
 who heard an accusation about his staff

354
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:10,360
 wasting his money or resources.

355
00:21:10,360 --> 00:21:15,360
 The word accused here might be implicating that.

356
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:19,720
 That is a false accusation happening here.

357
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:24,480
 And his immediate response was to lay off his staff.

358
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:27,960
 We see the story is very messed up

359
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:30,280
 in the first sentence, right?

360
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:33,000
 So the manager, without any opportunity

361
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,800
 to explain or defend himself,

362
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:38,840
 he immediately thinks about how he should respond

363
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,720
 to this situation.

364
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:44,040
 Apparently, he still gets a notice period.

365
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:49,040
 So he's still in the office as a manager of the rich man,

366
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:53,320
 and out of his fear about the future,

367
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:57,600
 he has decided to take advantage of his position,

368
00:21:57,600 --> 00:22:02,400
 to lower the debt of his master's debtors

369
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:06,240
 so that those people owe him a favor

370
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:10,080
 which could possibly benefit him in the future.

371
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:14,520
 In the Greco-Roman society, there's a culture

372
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:17,680
 which when someone gives you a favor,

373
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:21,720
 you're almost obliged to give back a higher favor.

374
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:24,640
 So this is what the manager is doing here.

375
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:29,120
 I wonder whether we can see the chain of effects here.

376
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:32,640
 In the manager's heart, he probably thinks,

377
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:35,560
 my boss is unfair to me.

378
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:40,240
 He trusted other people instead of me.

379
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:44,800
 He did not even give me a chance to explain

380
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,440
 before laying me off.

381
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:49,760
 So I'm just gonna use my position

382
00:22:49,760 --> 00:22:54,480
 for my own benefit one last time.

383
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:57,040
 It's not my fault, but his.

384
00:22:58,320 --> 00:23:00,200
 It sounds familiar, right?

385
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:03,200
 It sounds like something that we would hear

386
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:07,640
 in our workplace, because my boss is unfair,

387
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:10,440
 so I'm gonna make it fair in my own way

388
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:14,720
 by slacking off perhaps, or by claiming more money

389
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:16,680
 than I should, et cetera, et cetera.

390
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:21,480
 So we see that when we suffer from the darkness

391
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:25,080
 of the world, it is actually an opportunity

392
00:23:25,080 --> 00:23:29,160
 for us to choose, to choose whether we follow

393
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:34,160
 the Christ-centered value, to demonstrate the integrity,

394
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:40,760
 or we can choose to follow the world's way,

395
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:44,480
 to own the values of the world,

396
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:47,520
 and to extend the suffering,

397
00:23:47,520 --> 00:23:50,320
 and make other people suffer as well.

398
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:55,760
 This parable is the example of being darkness

399
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:58,840
 in the darkness, and a tasteless salt.

400
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:02,600
 And there's one more detail I would like us

401
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:04,960
 to look into, which is the action

402
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:09,920
 of reducing the debt amount, and the master's response.

403
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:13,400
 There are different debates from different scholars

404
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:17,400
 on how the manager reduced the debt amount.

405
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:20,920
 Some people said he is actually reducing

406
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:24,440
 the high interest involved in the debt.

407
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:28,440
 And some people said he is actually

408
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:31,080
 maybe eliminating the commissions

409
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:33,880
 that are supposed for him.

410
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:36,880
 So actually he is doing a good thing.

411
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:40,600
 And in fact, at the end, the master commended him

412
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:41,920
 for acting smartly.

413
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:46,240
 What he did, by actually benefiting

414
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:48,880
 for all parties in this story,

415
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:51,720
 the debtors, they are paying less.

416
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:56,200
 The master, it's seen to be a generous man,

417
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,760
 like gaining his reputation.

418
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:02,080
 And the manager is commended by his master.

419
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:04,520
 So it's a win-win-win situation.

420
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:07,840
 We don't know the details about interest

421
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:12,680
 and commission part, but I want us to see that.

422
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:17,120
 Jesus clearly say that his intention

423
00:25:17,120 --> 00:25:21,480
 was to find security after losing his job.

424
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:26,080
 And in verse eight, he described the manager

425
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:28,840
 as a dishonest manager.

426
00:25:28,840 --> 00:25:33,520
 So it could be true that he is doing a good thing

427
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:36,000
 for everyone, for his master.

428
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:40,400
 And it could be true that his work is shrewd.

429
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:46,320
 But Jesus also takes his honesty in his account.

430
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:52,320
 And Jesus cannot unsee his dishonesty in his heart.

431
00:25:52,320 --> 00:26:00,880
 Same to us, Jesus wants the whole of us.

432
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:05,120
 He does not only see the product of our work,

433
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:07,160
 but also our hearts.

434
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:10,920
 I wonder how it speaks to us.

435
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:15,120
 I'm sure we're experiencing different things

436
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:16,320
 in our workplace.

437
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:18,920
 It doesn't always have to be dishonesty

438
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:21,640
 or false accusation happening around.

439
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:27,800
 But we could do all the right things in people's eyes

440
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:31,320
 and follow all the things that our work requires us to do.

441
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:35,800
 We can have great influence to the people around us

442
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:37,720
 and to the society even.

443
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:43,280
 But are we demonstrating the values that we believe?

444
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:48,280
 Are we doing the right thing with the right intention

445
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:51,000
 even when no one sees that?

446
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:56,280
 How are we making choices when we are facing

447
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:58,440
 different situations at our work,

448
00:26:58,440 --> 00:27:00,800
 especially difficult situations?

449
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:05,480
 Will we choose to uphold our values

450
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:11,280
 even if those are unpopular among our workplaces?

451
00:27:12,280 --> 00:27:16,920
 So I want to share a story about myself

452
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:20,640
 where there was a time I found my values

453
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:25,160
 were fairly unpopular in my workplace.

454
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:27,400
 There was a time that I really struggled

455
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:29,480
 with my work environment.

456
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:32,760
 So it was the time that I changed from working

457
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:35,560
 in a law firm to in-house.

458
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:38,000
 So the difference is in a law firm,

459
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:42,000
 90% of our colleagues are legal professionals.

460
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:46,120
 So you kind of have similar values

461
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:51,080
 or the professional conduct that we are all following.

462
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:56,080
 But in-house instead is a commercial company.

463
00:27:56,080 --> 00:27:59,000
 So I work in the legal department.

464
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:04,000
 So 95% of my colleagues were not legal professional

465
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:06,040
 and only two of us are.

466
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:10,520
 So that's the environment I find myself

467
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:11,840
 really struggle with.

468
00:28:11,840 --> 00:28:12,840
 So I will tell you why.

469
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:14,760
 There are three reasons, there are three things

470
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:17,040
 I really struggle with and I still remember.

471
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:21,120
 And first thing, I really don't understand till today.

472
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:22,640
 So if anyone understand that,

473
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:24,440
 can you tell me after the service?

474
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:29,040
 So I don't know why the staff there are very obsessed

475
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:31,760
 with knowing the confidential information.

476
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:37,680
 So the people will come to me, try to make friends

477
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:39,720
 and then they will ask me,

478
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:41,760
 oh, tell me something confidential,

479
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:44,480
 like something like HR movement

480
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:49,480
 or personal data of a certain staff in our team.

481
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:53,720
 And then I'm like, but confidentiality

482
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:57,360
 is one of my biggest commitment to my work

483
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:59,080
 as a legal professional, right?

484
00:28:59,080 --> 00:29:01,280
 So I can't do that.

485
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:05,040
 And I'm like, I really don't understand.

486
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:06,440
 But there are more things.

487
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:11,200
 The second thing is, there are constantly people come

488
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:15,560
 and tell me that I supposed to be doing certain things,

489
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:18,640
 but clearly those are not within the legal scope.

490
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:21,080
 So I don't think that's the case.

491
00:29:21,080 --> 00:29:24,640
 So I feel like I'm a person with good boundaries.

492
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:27,520
 So I'm okay with saying no.

493
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:28,600
 So that's what I did.

494
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:30,240
 I tried to say no and people would tell me,

495
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:31,640
 oh, this is something you should do.

496
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:34,360
 I'm like, no, I don't think so.

497
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:37,760
 But here's the third thing that I really struggle with.

498
00:29:37,760 --> 00:29:41,800
 Whenever I say no, no matter it's to the confidential things

499
00:29:41,800 --> 00:29:45,840
 or to do certain things I don't supposed to do,

500
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:47,240
 people will say this to me.

501
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,080
 I'm not kidding.

502
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:49,360
 Throughout more than two years,

503
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:52,720
 people say this until I leave the company.

504
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:54,280
 And they say this to me.

505
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:59,800
 The previous person in your position would do that.

506
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:02,520
 And I'm like, what?

507
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:03,680
 And they go on, they go on.

508
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:05,040
 This is the worst part.

509
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:09,160
 They would tell me, she is popular among the company,

510
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,120
 but not you.

511
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:15,520
 And I'm like, ouch, what have I done?

512
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:20,520
 And it really hurts me and I really struggle

513
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:22,920
 with the fact that I'm hearing this,

514
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:25,560
 if not every week, every other week.

515
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:28,000
 And I'm like, no, I wasn't like that.

516
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,520
 When I was in law firm, I had good relationship

517
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:32,320
 with my colleagues.

518
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:35,720
 What's wrong with me now?

519
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:37,520
 And I really struggle with,

520
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:41,000
 am I supposed to do those things they are telling me?

521
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:42,440
 So I really struggle.

522
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:44,000
 So of course I pray.

523
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:46,720
 And then there was one night I was praying

524
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:50,480
 and Jesus actually remind me of a conversation

525
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:53,520
 at the very beginning when I did the legal training.

526
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:57,840
 And he reminded me that, he said this to me,

527
00:30:57,840 --> 00:31:01,200
 "Jennifer, I want you to be different.

528
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:05,520
 "Not in a sense that you need to be rebelliously different

529
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:10,240
 "from everyone else, but I want you to be able

530
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:14,120
 "to discern what is the right thing to do,

531
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:18,680
 "even when everyone else is telling you the opposite."

532
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:25,000
 So that was a very timely reminder from God

533
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:28,800
 when I was really struggling in my workplace.

534
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:33,360
 And then from that moment on, I have to make a decision.

535
00:31:33,360 --> 00:31:34,880
 I have to choose as well,

536
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:38,360
 whether I follow all the voices around me

537
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:41,800
 or I follow the voice from God.

538
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:44,280
 And of course I could not bear the result

539
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:48,000
 of not listening to God when he clearly speaks to me.

540
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:51,800
 So I try, I try to hold on to my values.

541
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:56,800
 I try to continue to do the work with my values from God

542
00:31:56,800 --> 00:32:04,360
 and also from my professional integrity as well.

543
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:10,760
 But at the end, I won't say I made a huge impact

544
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:14,520
 in that company, but God really, by his grace,

545
00:32:14,520 --> 00:32:18,360
 showed me very close to the end of my time there,

546
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:22,680
 like what impact did I make with upholding my values.

547
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:25,440
 So I remember there was one colleague, she came to me.

548
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:28,960
 We didn't talk, we didn't talk much throughout the years

549
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,240
 that we worked there.

550
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:33,360
 But one day she approached me and she said,

551
00:32:33,360 --> 00:32:41,000
 "Jennifer, I see you demonstrating a different value

552
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:43,760
 "and a different approach to work,

553
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:47,400
 "that you are not a fan of pleasing people,

554
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:53,400
 "and I'm not like work as in I need to help everyone

555
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:56,520
 "to do their work, but I want people to learn

556
00:32:56,520 --> 00:33:01,520
 "how to grow, how to do their work in their areas of work,

557
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:05,040
 "which I think is a healthy thing for our company.

558
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:06,920
 "And then the other thing I see in you

559
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:09,200
 "is you don't really compromise

560
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:12,480
 "no matter how people commented on you."

561
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:15,280
 And that motivated that colleague,

562
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:20,280
 motivated her to uphold her values in her role as well.

563
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:24,560
 So I don't know how the story is down to you.

564
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:26,440
 Perhaps you're expecting a testimony

565
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:30,400
 with a bigger or more immediate impact.

566
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:35,360
 But I want to say that each of us constantly live

567
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:40,360
 in the tension between the values of the world and of Christ.

568
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:44,480
 And the world and the people around you

569
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:48,120
 is going to tell you what you're supposed to do

570
00:33:48,120 --> 00:33:52,120
 and how you should act in your company.

571
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:57,560
 And we will need to choose whether we follow,

572
00:33:57,560 --> 00:34:04,880
 whether we follow those voices or we follow Jesus's voice.

573
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:07,480
 So it might look different in your context.

574
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:09,080
 Let me give you some examples.

575
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:12,960
 If you work in academia, everyone might be telling you

576
00:34:12,960 --> 00:34:15,560
 that you need to focus on writing your papers,

577
00:34:15,560 --> 00:34:19,920
 publish more to earn your academic reputation.

578
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:23,320
 If you're a salesperson, people around you might tell you

579
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:25,440
 that you need to reach a target,

580
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:28,360
 you need to get the most money out of the pocket

581
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:30,200
 from the person in front of you

582
00:34:30,200 --> 00:34:32,920
 or the company that you're working with.

583
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:36,320
 Or if you are doing office routine work,

584
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:40,680
 people might tell you, "Just follow what everyone else does.

585
00:34:40,680 --> 00:34:42,400
 "Don't ask any questions."

586
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:45,920
 But I want to ask us,

587
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:50,040
 I want us to constantly ask ourselves this question.

588
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:53,520
 What does Jesus say about it?

589
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:58,200
 To those voices, to those questions,

590
00:34:58,200 --> 00:35:01,360
 to those things that people are constantly telling you

591
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:02,560
 who you should be.

592
00:35:02,560 --> 00:35:06,960
 And I don't think I have a simple answer

593
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:09,440
 for these questions or I don't have a formula

594
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,360
 for you to follow.

595
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:15,240
 We do ABC, then we are showing the Christ-centered integrity

596
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:20,240
 but it is a start of a conversation between you and Jesus

597
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:23,960
 and it will take a long-term effort.

598
00:35:23,960 --> 00:35:25,960
 It is not like we do something nice

599
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:27,320
 and we check off the box,

600
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:30,040
 then we can demonstrate the values.

601
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:35,040
 Demonstrating the value of Jesus requires two things,

602
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:38,000
 commitment and persistence.

603
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:43,560
 First, we need to commit to constantly seek

604
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:47,520
 what is fitting in Jesus' eyes.

605
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:51,760
 And then we need to choose to persist

606
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:54,760
 in following his voice as we work.

607
00:35:54,760 --> 00:36:00,380
 When it comes to the calling of being sought and light,

608
00:36:00,380 --> 00:36:02,840
 it takes consistent effort.

609
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:08,560
 We need to persist our faith and our value

610
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:12,960
 in long-term basis and we can expect 100%

611
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:16,080
 we will face challenges and temptations

612
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:18,640
 at some point of our lives.

613
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:22,960
 And we need to always challenge the mindset of,

614
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:26,080
 everyone else is doing that so I'm gonna do the same.

615
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:31,920
 You might be thinking, ah, not sure about that, what if?

616
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:35,160
 I suffer even more if I work differently.

617
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:37,320
 Or what if my boss and my colleagues

618
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:39,000
 would take advantage of me

619
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:43,440
 if I work differently in my environment?

620
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:46,800
 And I want to say this to us.

621
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:53,080
 To follow Jesus is also to extend the grace

622
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:56,460
 and the light we have received from him.

623
00:36:56,460 --> 00:37:00,700
 And the grace that we have received already

624
00:37:00,700 --> 00:37:03,680
 has changed our lives.

625
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:07,580
 And it is our turn to be sought and light,

626
00:37:07,580 --> 00:37:10,520
 to be different from the world

627
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:15,380
 and change the state of blondness or darkness around us.

628
00:37:15,380 --> 00:37:18,920
 And see, this is the purpose

629
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:21,380
 as we are doing our actual work.

630
00:37:21,380 --> 00:37:25,020
 We are demonstrating the light,

631
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:31,320
 the hope and the grace to people around us,

632
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:35,340
 although we don't always see it.

633
00:37:35,340 --> 00:37:38,740
 And we will need to hold on to Jesus by faith

634
00:37:38,740 --> 00:37:40,180
 to be able to do that.

635
00:37:40,180 --> 00:37:47,080
 So I really encourage us to really think about it,

636
00:37:47,080 --> 00:37:49,820
 to ask Jesus the question,

637
00:37:49,820 --> 00:37:53,580
 what do you say about the values?

638
00:37:53,580 --> 00:37:56,360
 What do you say about our work?

639
00:37:56,360 --> 00:38:00,960
 So I've shared my story on this.

640
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:04,940
 In this sermon series, we think it will be nice,

641
00:38:04,940 --> 00:38:07,000
 it will be helpful for us to hear the voice

642
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:08,860
 from our community as well.

643
00:38:08,860 --> 00:38:11,820
 So today we've invited Chris Webster,

644
00:38:11,820 --> 00:38:14,400
 who is also a great leader in his industry,

645
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:18,540
 to share his story on how God called him

646
00:38:18,540 --> 00:38:22,700
 to live out a different value in the city of Hong Kong.

647
00:38:22,700 --> 00:38:26,440
 So would you join me to invite Chris to the stage, please?

648
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:29,600
 (audience applauding)

649
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:34,100
 Over to you, Chris.

650
00:38:34,100 --> 00:38:36,660
 - Thank you very much, Jennifer.

651
00:38:36,660 --> 00:38:38,100
 That was amazing.

652
00:38:38,100 --> 00:38:44,060
 Integrity, the out, yeah, out,

653
00:38:44,060 --> 00:38:48,260
 when you live as Christ in the workplace.

654
00:38:48,260 --> 00:38:49,560
 How do you cope with that?

655
00:38:50,540 --> 00:38:54,100
 I want to share a spiritual life hack

656
00:38:54,100 --> 00:38:56,240
 that God gave me a long time ago.

657
00:38:56,240 --> 00:39:00,080
 First of all, Moses.

658
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:04,040
 Somewhat over 3,000 years ago,

659
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:10,060
 Moses spent his amazing 40 days, 40 nights

660
00:39:10,060 --> 00:39:15,240
 on a mountainside preparing for his new career.

661
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:16,080
 Can you hear me?

662
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:18,100
 I've got a bit of a bad throat, thank you.

663
00:39:19,220 --> 00:39:22,080
 It was Moses's second career change,

664
00:39:22,080 --> 00:39:26,420
 and God was very, very merciful to him.

665
00:39:26,420 --> 00:39:30,940
 He downloaded such a lot of information

666
00:39:30,940 --> 00:39:33,340
 to give Moses a clue.

667
00:39:33,340 --> 00:39:38,920
 Everything, social relationships, economic relationships,

668
00:39:38,920 --> 00:39:43,980
 excuse me, the judiciary, the rules for the judiciary,

669
00:39:43,980 --> 00:39:45,760
 the rules for the executive,

670
00:39:46,660 --> 00:39:49,700
 laws over life and death, religion, et cetera.

671
00:39:49,700 --> 00:39:57,800
 First takeaway, possibly, you're going into a new job.

672
00:39:57,800 --> 00:40:02,400
 Download from God what God wants you from that job.

673
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:06,300
 You're going to a new work week.

674
00:40:06,300 --> 00:40:10,480
 Download what God wants for you that week.

675
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:16,100
 11 years as dean at Hong Kong U.

676
00:40:16,100 --> 00:40:18,620
 I'm a professor in Hong Kong U still.

677
00:40:18,620 --> 00:40:24,380
 If I had a difficult day, if I had a difficult week,

678
00:40:24,380 --> 00:40:26,220
 I would get up an hour earlier.

679
00:40:26,220 --> 00:40:28,540
 I'd get going two hours earlier

680
00:40:28,540 --> 00:40:32,460
 and make sure I had downloaded what God wanted to say.

681
00:40:32,460 --> 00:40:36,660
 It cuts short meetings very, very efficiently.

682
00:40:36,660 --> 00:40:38,860
 So Moses got that.

683
00:40:38,860 --> 00:40:41,260
 It's recorded in Exodus.

684
00:40:41,260 --> 00:40:44,860
 In the chapters that record it in Exodus,

685
00:40:44,860 --> 00:40:49,060
 there is at the end of that a little pause and summary

686
00:40:49,060 --> 00:40:52,380
 before moving on to describe just how atrociously

687
00:40:52,380 --> 00:40:56,140
 the Hebrews behaved after Moses came down from the mountain,

688
00:40:56,140 --> 00:40:57,480
 golden calf and everything.

689
00:40:57,480 --> 00:41:04,460
 What would God choose to repeat, to summarize?

690
00:41:04,460 --> 00:41:06,280
 The first great commandment,

691
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:10,460
 the laws of sacrifice,

692
00:41:10,460 --> 00:41:14,340
 the anticipate Jesus' own sacrifice?

693
00:41:14,340 --> 00:41:19,340
 No, actually, the fourth commandment, Sabbath.

694
00:41:19,340 --> 00:41:27,940
 Almost as long ago, when I was doing my A-levels in London,

695
00:41:27,940 --> 00:41:34,980
 Jesus whispered in my ear a little challenge.

696
00:41:34,980 --> 00:41:38,740
 He said, "Will you live your life and your career

697
00:41:38,740 --> 00:41:40,620
 "by the spirit of the Sabbath?"

698
00:41:40,620 --> 00:41:42,740
 Spirit of the Sabbath.

699
00:41:42,740 --> 00:41:44,980
 We all know what the law of the Sabbath is.

700
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:47,460
 Let me tell you what the spirit of Sabbath

701
00:41:47,460 --> 00:41:49,060
 at least meant for me.

702
00:41:49,060 --> 00:41:50,820
 Excuse me.

703
00:41:50,820 --> 00:41:54,460
 We have seven days a week to do anything.

704
00:41:54,460 --> 00:41:58,500
 Seven days, Hebrews, seven days a week to plow,

705
00:41:58,500 --> 00:42:03,500
 to plant, to water, to fertilize, to harvest,

706
00:42:03,500 --> 00:42:04,780
 to collect the straw.

707
00:42:04,780 --> 00:42:08,060
 I've worked in the harvest on a farm.

708
00:42:08,060 --> 00:42:10,140
 I know that seven days is important.

709
00:42:10,140 --> 00:42:14,460
 You do not miss the seventh day of a week.

710
00:42:14,460 --> 00:42:17,940
 At Hong Kong, students, university, school,

711
00:42:17,940 --> 00:42:21,740
 everybody around you will be studying,

712
00:42:21,740 --> 00:42:23,580
 working for seven days.

713
00:42:23,580 --> 00:42:28,020
 You will be at a disadvantage if you Sabbath, right?

714
00:42:28,020 --> 00:42:29,260
 Naturally speaking.

715
00:42:29,260 --> 00:42:34,740
 Supernaturally speaking, God will always come through

716
00:42:34,740 --> 00:42:36,460
 for you, that's the spirit.

717
00:42:36,460 --> 00:42:37,620
 It's trust.

718
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:41,680
 The Sabbath is a kind of manifestation

719
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:44,120
 of the great virtue of meekness.

720
00:42:44,120 --> 00:42:49,120
 Meekness means you have power, you have resources,

721
00:42:49,120 --> 00:42:51,320
 but you choose not to use it.

722
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:54,840
 One of Jesus' greatest characteristics

723
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,680
 in his incarnation.

724
00:42:56,680 --> 00:43:00,560
 He laid down his majesty and became son of man

725
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:03,560
 and son of God, and God raised him up.

726
00:43:03,560 --> 00:43:08,040
 So I did A-levels.

727
00:43:08,960 --> 00:43:11,600
 I tried very hard.

728
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:14,760
 Saturday, I would stop revising,

729
00:43:14,760 --> 00:43:16,520
 take a Sabbath on the Sunday.

730
00:43:16,520 --> 00:43:19,840
 Not necessarily a Sunday, 'cause it's not legal, remember?

731
00:43:19,840 --> 00:43:20,960
 It's principle.

732
00:43:20,960 --> 00:43:24,880
 First degree, undergraduate degree.

733
00:43:24,880 --> 00:43:27,600
 Degree exams coming up the next day.

734
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:32,820
 On a Monday, clear the revision by Saturday.

735
00:43:32,820 --> 00:43:37,560
 Postgraduate degrees, work interviews,

736
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:40,200
 preparing for that massive talk I've got to give

737
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:42,080
 in Europe somewhere.

738
00:43:42,080 --> 00:43:46,160
 Sabbath, quiet, peace, trust.

739
00:43:46,160 --> 00:43:50,160
 It's all about trusting God.

740
00:43:50,160 --> 00:43:55,680
 So how does that impact on all the things

741
00:43:55,680 --> 00:43:58,160
 that Jennifer has talked about?

742
00:43:58,160 --> 00:44:00,360
 'Cause that's my discipline, okay?

743
00:44:00,360 --> 00:44:03,740
 It's not going in and evangelizing.

744
00:44:03,740 --> 00:44:06,460
 It's not going into work and telling people

745
00:44:06,460 --> 00:44:09,160
 what a great religious Christian I am.

746
00:44:09,160 --> 00:44:12,380
 How does it impact?

747
00:44:12,380 --> 00:44:15,960
 Well, I think it impacts like this, essentially.

748
00:44:15,960 --> 00:44:19,840
 Revelations 19.

749
00:44:19,840 --> 00:44:26,000
 The spirit of prophecy is the testimony of Jesus.

750
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:28,160
 It reads the other way around as well.

751
00:44:28,160 --> 00:44:31,380
 The testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy.

752
00:44:31,380 --> 00:44:35,000
 When you take time out like that,

753
00:44:36,020 --> 00:44:38,880
 you fast, you pray, you Sabbath.

754
00:44:38,880 --> 00:44:42,880
 You draw close to Jesus and the Father,

755
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:46,260
 the Son and the Holy Spirit draws close to you.

756
00:44:46,260 --> 00:44:50,240
 And you don't tell people that you're doing it.

757
00:44:50,240 --> 00:44:54,860
 Like praying and fasting, Sabbathing is a secret thing.

758
00:44:54,860 --> 00:44:57,320
 Jesus says, do it in secret.

759
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:59,600
 And your Father who is in heaven

760
00:44:59,600 --> 00:45:04,280
 will see and reward you in heaven

761
00:45:04,280 --> 00:45:06,220
 for what you're doing in secret.

762
00:45:06,220 --> 00:45:07,640
 And how does he reward you?

763
00:45:07,640 --> 00:45:11,480
 He gives you more of the spirit of prophecy,

764
00:45:11,480 --> 00:45:13,820
 more of the spirit of Jesus.

765
00:45:13,820 --> 00:45:18,820
 And then you go into work and you find that, excuse me,

766
00:45:18,820 --> 00:45:23,460
 you find that your own shabby integrity

767
00:45:23,460 --> 00:45:26,780
 falls like dirty rags from you.

768
00:45:26,780 --> 00:45:29,740
 And it is the integrity of Jesus

769
00:45:29,740 --> 00:45:33,020
 embodied in the Holy Spirit that empowers you.

770
00:45:33,020 --> 00:45:37,680
 You become sharper, you become more loving, kinder boss.

771
00:45:37,680 --> 00:45:42,440
 You become wiser, you become more just,

772
00:45:42,440 --> 00:45:46,400
 better able to balance judgment and mercy.

773
00:45:46,400 --> 00:45:49,120
 I think that's a great definition of justice.

774
00:45:49,120 --> 00:45:52,640
 Justice is only fully embodied in Jesus Christ.

775
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:54,940
 So you have the spirit of Jesus on you.

776
00:45:54,940 --> 00:45:59,940
 You become a just person, you balance judgment and mercy.

777
00:46:00,900 --> 00:46:02,760
 You become a better servant,

778
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:06,060
 whether you're a leader or a follower, you're a servant.

779
00:46:06,060 --> 00:46:10,480
 And the body of Christ becomes your body and your spirit.

780
00:46:10,480 --> 00:46:13,800
 Thank you very much.

781
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:16,960
 (audience applauding)

782
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:20,920
 - Thank you so much, Chris.

783
00:46:20,920 --> 00:46:25,720
 So Chris really demonstrated a very, very different value

784
00:46:25,720 --> 00:46:28,540
 from the city of Hong Kong, from Hong Kong of people,

785
00:46:28,540 --> 00:46:31,560
 to really be obedient to God's command

786
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:33,680
 on Sabbath, on resting.

787
00:46:33,680 --> 00:46:38,320
 So I'm sure the different stories will speak to us

788
00:46:38,320 --> 00:46:40,460
 and each person, we have different stories,

789
00:46:40,460 --> 00:46:45,080
 we have different areas that we are working on.

790
00:46:45,080 --> 00:46:48,480
 And I'm sure God has different things to say to you

791
00:46:48,480 --> 00:46:51,200
 in terms of the specific, unique things

792
00:46:51,200 --> 00:46:53,360
 that you are going through right now.

793
00:46:53,360 --> 00:46:56,000
 So right now I would like to close us in prayer.

794
00:46:56,000 --> 00:46:58,160
 Can I invite you all to stand

795
00:46:58,160 --> 00:47:00,820
 and we would like to pray together.

796
00:47:00,820 --> 00:47:05,520
 So first of all, I want to pray for those

797
00:47:05,520 --> 00:47:09,080
 who feel you're really struggling at work.

798
00:47:09,080 --> 00:47:14,080
 You struggle to see God, to even continue to work.

799
00:47:14,080 --> 00:47:18,840
 So at the moment we will pray for you.

800
00:47:18,840 --> 00:47:22,860
 So if you are one of that, encourage you to also,

801
00:47:22,860 --> 00:47:25,520
 to bring your struggles to God as well

802
00:47:25,520 --> 00:47:30,280
 and ask him for his grace for you to continue

803
00:47:30,280 --> 00:47:36,360
 and to see what God has for you in the coming season.

804
00:47:36,360 --> 00:47:40,520
 And I also want to pray for us

805
00:47:40,520 --> 00:47:44,400
 on how we are hearing different voices

806
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:47,380
 from the world when we work.

807
00:47:47,380 --> 00:47:51,880
 And we'll pray for you that you will hear God's voice

808
00:47:51,880 --> 00:47:56,880
 clearly and to be filled by the Holy Spirit,

809
00:47:56,880 --> 00:48:03,760
 to really uphold his value, to be his salt and light

810
00:48:03,760 --> 00:48:07,900
 because with our own strength, we can't do that.

811
00:48:07,900 --> 00:48:11,400
 So let's pray together.

812
00:48:11,400 --> 00:48:15,260
 Jesus, we thank you.

813
00:48:15,260 --> 00:48:18,300
 We thank you that you called us to work.

814
00:48:18,300 --> 00:48:21,600
 You give us purpose to work.

815
00:48:22,600 --> 00:48:27,600
 And you allow us to be part of your redemptive work.

816
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:30,760
 We thank you for that.

817
00:48:30,760 --> 00:48:33,800
 And Lord, we want to right now live up our brothers

818
00:48:33,800 --> 00:48:37,360
 and sisters who are struggling with their workplace,

819
00:48:37,360 --> 00:48:40,200
 maybe their work environment,

820
00:48:40,200 --> 00:48:43,140
 or maybe their intense hours of the work.

821
00:48:43,140 --> 00:48:46,660
 Lord, we ask for your grace.

822
00:48:47,640 --> 00:48:51,920
 We ask that your grace will be enough for each of us

823
00:48:51,920 --> 00:48:57,520
 to be able to continue to flourish in our workplace,

824
00:48:57,520 --> 00:48:59,000
 to be able to see you,

825
00:48:59,000 --> 00:49:01,540
 to see your purposes in our workplace.

826
00:49:01,540 --> 00:49:05,800
 So Jesus, we ask that you come and help us,

827
00:49:05,800 --> 00:49:11,720
 especially to help those who are suffering among us.

828
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:18,840
 And Jesus, we want to live up all the work environment,

829
00:49:18,840 --> 00:49:23,560
 struggles, all the different voices that we hear each day.

830
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:26,640
 And we confess that those voices sometimes

831
00:49:26,640 --> 00:49:28,080
 impact us as well.

832
00:49:28,080 --> 00:49:33,080
 Sometimes we are unable to hear your voice because of that.

833
00:49:33,080 --> 00:49:36,160
 But Lord, would you help us?

834
00:49:36,160 --> 00:49:41,760
 We come and we ask the questions to you that,

835
00:49:41,760 --> 00:49:45,280
 what do you say about my work?

836
00:49:45,280 --> 00:49:49,920
 What do you say about the values,

837
00:49:49,920 --> 00:49:53,280
 the words that we are hearing each day?

838
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:55,360
 We want to hear you.

839
00:49:55,360 --> 00:49:58,280
 So Jesus, would you speak to us on that?

840
00:49:58,280 --> 00:50:05,400
 And also we want to ask for your spirit to fill us.

841
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:10,160
 We pray that you will allow us to grow

842
00:50:10,160 --> 00:50:14,560
 in hearing your voice and in persisting to do your work,

843
00:50:14,560 --> 00:50:17,040
 to be more like you in our work.

844
00:50:17,040 --> 00:50:20,800
 Holy Spirit, we ask for your help

845
00:50:20,800 --> 00:50:25,080
 because we acknowledge our limitation.

846
00:50:25,080 --> 00:50:29,380
 With our own strength, it's impossible for us to do that.

847
00:50:29,380 --> 00:50:32,400
 So Holy Spirit, we call for your power.

848
00:50:32,400 --> 00:50:34,600
 We call for your wisdom.

849
00:50:34,600 --> 00:50:38,040
 We call for your strength to fill us,

850
00:50:38,040 --> 00:50:43,040
 to allow us to work for you each day.

851
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:51,440
 And we pray that your grace is enough for us each day.

852
00:50:51,440 --> 00:50:56,760
 And we pray in Jesus' name, amen.

